{{velocity}} = Welcome = Welcome to Propaganda Tactics!
Want to know what tricks the media is using to fool their readers, viewers, and listeners? You've come to the right place. We break down misleading [[Articles]], showing you specifically what [[Tactics]] they use to mislead you.
= Articles = We currently have #showCount('PArticleClass', 'Articles') [[Articles]], which are deceptive opinion pieces, magazine articles, and TV and radio transcripts. Each article looks something like this: (% style="border-style: solid;" %) ((( [[image:sampleArticle.PNG||width=800]] )))
= Quotes = For each Article, we select deceptive quotes, provide a rebuttal to the quote, and tag each quote with one or more [[Tactics>>Tactics]]. There are currently #showCount('PSourceClass', 'Articles') individual quotes.
For example, here's a random quote: (% style="border-style: solid; padding: 25px;" %) ((( #showRandomQuote() )))
= Sources = Each Article comes from a particular [[Source>>Sources]], and we currently list #showCount('PSourceClass', 'Sources') sources. For a given Source, you can see the list of Articles and a list of Authors (employees) of that source. Want to see the most common Tactics used by [[Sources.Fox News]]? We have that.
Here's a sample: (% style="border-style: solid;" %) ((( [[image:sampleSource.PNG||width=400]] )))
= Authors = Each [[Article>>Articles]] is written or spoken by an [[Author>>Authors]], and we currently list #showCount('PAuthorClass', 'Authors') authors. Want to see if [[Authors.Sean Hannity]]'s favorite tactic is [[Tactics.Cheerleading]]? We have that.
(% style="border-style: solid;" %) ((( [[image:sampleAuthor.PNG||width=400]] )))
= Tactics = We have come up with #showCount('TacticClass', 'Tactics') [[Tactics]], each grouped into one of #showCount('PCategoryClass', 'Categories') [[Categories]]. For example, the [[Tactics.Lie Of Omission.WebHome]] tactic is in the [[Categories.Lie]] category.
(% style="border-style: solid;" %) ((( [[image:sampleTactic.PNG||width=800]] ))) {{/velocity}}
